                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1082">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">831.00/7–1946</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-19T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 19, 1946—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>409. We are gratified Colombian President was fully informed Dawson conversation
                    and as stated previous telegrams believe any other course might have exposed us
                    to serious difficulties. We believe that if any further steps are contemplated
                    they likewise should be fully and frankly discussed with Colombia, either
                    through your colleague in Caracas or through Ambassador Wiley Bogotá.</p>
                <p>Repeated Caracas.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
